&gt; Half blown by the boom, half running, Trelos let out a help as he flew
across the open area in front of the government tower and slammed head-first
into the side of a building.  With a growl, he transformed back into beast
mode and began to run toward the enemy, still not quite sure where it was.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I think we should pull out.&quot; said Ravenchief.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;No argument there,&quot; said Depthcharge, holding one hand up to his ear,
still reeling from the shockwave.
&gt;
&gt; Both transformed and began a mostly-verical flight out of the city.

OOC: Keep in mind the mecha-lion is NOT invisible or cloaked, his shielding
had failed a few posts ago.

BIC:

The lion looked winded, if a mechanical beast could actually be out of
breath. For a moment its systems flickered as power shifted from one system
to the next as he recovered his stance. His tail flicked in obvious
disappointment and annoyance, his opponent had not been destroyed as he had
hoped.

With a powerful roar, that while not anywhere near as powerful as the
previous one still managed to shatter a few of the remaining windows. The
lion leaped off the perch he had been on and began to run at Trelos. If the
large mecha-lion was aware of the grenade launchers that were at his
shoulders, or the fact that he had any other modes or weapons, he was
certainly not using them. Instead he bared his teeth and then roared again
as he ran to battle!

